In general, database setup is done in these steps,

* Download and install a JDBC driver
* Create a database
* Add datasource entries to the Postxdb configuration file

Postxdb comes equipped with the H2 database and with PostgreSQL connectivity.
No driver has to be downloaded for them.

Postxdb creates and uses only three tables. Their names are prefixed by @pxd_@

Pick the subsection that corresponds to the database engine of your choice.
